      "description": "This build works really well for the EXP lane because it gives a solid balance of damage and sustain, which helps a lot with my rotations when I’m using Yin. I usually start by cutting the lane, especially if I’m up against sustain-heavy fighters like Yu Zhong, Ruby, or Phoveus. Doing this lets me control the wave early and rotate faster to help my team.\n\nIf I’m facing squishier fighters like Guinevere or Zilong, I switch to the Fighter Emblem for higher damage. It’s a more aggressive setup, but it still gives enough sustain to stay in fights.\n\nFor items, I like to build Fury Hammer first so I can get early penetration. After that, I go for Sea Halberd since it’s a big help for Yin, especially against enemies with sustain.\n\nAs for spells, Petrify is a must-have because it helps extend your crowd control and makes it easier to secure kills. But depending on your playstyle or role, you can also use Flicker, Execute, or even Retribution if you’re going jungle.\n\nOverall, this setup keeps Yin flexible and effective, no matter the matchup.",
